01:35:00,129 --> 01:35:04,361
Yeah, well, I had something going
in that picture, but it missed.

727
01:35:05,329 --> 01:35:08,002
I had something going
in The Deep too, but it just missed.

728
01:35:08,169 --> 01:35:10,683
- The Deep was a kiss-ass to Still.
- No one asked you!

729
01:35:10,849 --> 01:35:13,158
Clyfford Still couldn't
polish Jackson's shoes.

730
01:35:13,329 --> 01:35:15,047
Look what you painted
when you were sober.

731
01:35:15,209 --> 01:35:17,484
Now that you're back on booze,
do you paint real pictures?

732
01:35:17,649 --> 01:35:20,004
- Climb off my back, bitch!
- You're a bum!

733
01:35:20,169 --> 01:35:24,401
- Open that mouth again, I'll kill you!
- You are killing me!

734
01:35:24,609 --> 01:35:27,169
Bitch! Bitch! Bitch! Bitch! Bitch!

735
01:35:27,329 --> 01:35:31,242
- You wouldn't have a child!
- That would have fixed everything.

736
01:35:31,449 --> 01:35:33,758
I never loved you!
Go fuck yourself!

737
01:35:33,929 --> 01:35:37,888
- I don't even wanna touch you!
- Your sex life is of no concern to me.

738
01:35:38,089 --> 01:35:40,887
Weekly trips to your therapist.
What a joke.

739
01:35:41,089 --> 01:35:44,968
And whatever trash you pick up at
the Cedar afterwards, I could care less!

740
01:35:45,129 --> 01:35:47,279
You don't wanna stay here.

741
01:35:47,449 --> 01:35:50,680
This is morning to night. This happens
over taking out the garbage!

742
01:35:50,849 --> 01:35:54,000
What are you looking for?
What are you pushing me for?

743
01:35:54,209 --> 01:35:55,881
Stop crying about it and paint!

744
01:35:56,089 --> 01:35:58,762
You're Jackson Pollock,
and you don't paint!

745
01:35:58,969 --> 01:36:01,278
It's a tragedy, and I can't stand it.

746
01:36:01,489 --> 01:36:02,604
Paint!

747
01:36:28,009 --> 01:36:30,079
- Hi.
- Hi.

748
01:36:43,889 --> 01:36:47,325
- You look great.
- Thanks. I missed you.

749
01:37:06,409 --> 01:37:10,800
- Don't look at me that way.
- I'm not looking at you.

750
01:37:14,569 --> 01:37:19,040
I was thinking we could visit Peggy
in Venice, see the Biennale.

751
01:37:19,409 --> 01:37:23,641
Time to go to Europe is when
you're very young or very old.

752
01:37:23,809 --> 01:37:25,845
But you should go.

753
01:37:26,009 --> 01:37:29,319
Everybody should do
what the hell they wanna do.

754
01:37:39,049 --> 01:37:43,839
She left it in the car.
I'm surprised she hasn't missed it.

755
01:37:44,009 --> 01:37:46,523
You take her
where our friends are.

756
01:37:46,689 --> 01:37:50,318
They have the good grace
not to tell me.

757
01:37:50,489 --> 01:37:53,049
If you don't stop seeing her,
I'm going to leave you.

758
01:37:53,209 --> 01:37:56,645
- I love her.
- You don't.

759
01:38:00,049 --> 01:38:01,562
She's my last chance.

760
01:38:05,649 --> 01:38:09,847
I am not going
to give you a divorce.

761
01:38:30,809 --> 01:38:33,164
If you could be anybody...

762
01:38:35,209 --> 01:38:40,567
...who ever lived in the history
of the whole world...

763
01:38:40,729 --> 01:38:43,448
...who would you be?

764
01:38:46,409 --> 01:38:48,206
You.

765
01:39:05,249 --> 01:39:08,207
I'd better get that.

766
01:39:34,689 --> 01:39:36,998
- Hello?
- I'm ridiculous.

767
01:39:37,169 --> 01:39:40,366
I think I left
my passport at the house.

768
01:39:40,529 --> 01:39:45,319
I suppose I'll have to wait
till the next sailing.

769
01:39:46,969 --> 01:39:48,960
Jackson?

770
01:39:51,489 --> 01:39:53,480
Pollock.

771
01:39:55,649 --> 01:40:00,769
Here it is.
I found it buried in my purse.

772
01:40:26,169 --> 01:40:29,559
I owe the woman something.

773
01:40:31,129 --> 01:40:34,041
I'd be dead without her.

774
01:40:35,009 --> 01:40:38,843
But I'm the one
who loves you, Jackson.

775
01:41:32,169 --> 01:41:38,517
The roses were
the most beautiful, deep red.

776
01:41:40,369 --> 01:41:43,679
I miss you and wish
you were sharing this with me.

777
01:41:43,849 --> 01:41:47,728
It would be wonderful
to get a note from you.

778
01:41:47,889 --> 01:41:52,087
The painting here
is unbelievably bad.

779
01:41:52,969 --> 01:41:55,688
How are you, Jackson?

780
01:41:56,569 --> 01:42:00,198
Kiss Gyp for me.
Love, Lee.

781
01:43:58,089 --> 01:44:00,762
It's okay, buddy.

782
01:44:06,609 --> 01:44:09,521
What have you got
there, Mr. Pollock?

783
01:44:09,689 --> 01:44:12,726
I found him hit on the road.

784
01:44:12,969 --> 01:44:15,802
He's a beautiful dog.

785
01:44:16,369 --> 01:44:18,678
You gotta save him.

786
01:44:18,849 --> 01:44:21,727
He's a beautiful dog.

787
01:44:36,969 --> 01:44:40,405
Keep a girl waiting,
why don't you.

788
01:44:42,689 --> 01:44:45,886
This is my friend Edith Metzger.

789
01:45:08,009 --> 01:45:12,958
Just throw your stuff in the back.
We can all fit in the front, I think.

790
01:45:15,889 --> 01:45:17,845
Thanks.

791
01:45:19,449 --> 01:45:22,725
Edith wants to go
to the beach today.

792
01:45:42,409 --> 01:45:45,162
We're all set and ready to go.

793
01:45:47,569 --> 01:45:49,480
You go.

794
01:45:55,409 --> 01:45:58,082
We'll wait for you.

795
01:46:02,809 --> 01:46:04,401
Okay?

796
01:46:20,329 --> 01:46:21,967
Are we going?

797
01:46:22,129 --> 01:46:26,441
He's taking a little nap.
He'll be down in a little bit.

798
01:46:26,689 --> 01:46:29,203
- Is he sick?
- No, he's fine. Come on.

799
01:46:29,369 --> 01:46:32,122
Let's go see the studio.

800
01:46:56,169 --> 01:46:58,046
What's doing for tonight?

801
01:46:58,209 --> 01:47:00,723
I'm invited to Ossorio's...

802
01:47:00,889 --> 01:47:04,120
...for a musicale
or something or other benefit.

803
01:47:04,289 --> 01:47:06,484
That could be fun. Let's go.

804
01:47:06,649 --> 01:47:09,368
I don't want to see
all those people.

805
01:47:09,529 --> 01:47:12,487
Come on, I wanna take
a picture with you.

806
01:47:12,649 --> 01:47:16,688
Edith, take our picture.

807
01:47:25,409 --> 01:47:27,320
Good.

808
01:47:33,209 --> 01:47:35,803
Okay, here we go.

809
01:47:37,329 --> 01:47:39,968
Leave the dishes.

810
01:47:40,129 --> 01:47:43,326
- Get dressed.
- We don't have to go, Jackson.

811
01:47:43,489 --> 01:47:49,166
- Really, you don't have to amuse me.
- Leave the dishes. Get dressed.

812
01:48:08,129 --> 01:48:11,087
What's the matter, Jackson?

813
01:48:15,089 --> 01:48:17,683
Are you all right?

814
01:48:51,249 --> 01:48:54,321
- I'm gonna call for help.
- Don't go in there.

815
01:48:54,489 --> 01:48:57,242
- I don't wanna drive with him.
- Get her back in the car.

816
01:48:57,409 --> 01:49:01,118
Come on, he's fine. I promise.
We're gonna go home.

817
01:49:01,289 --> 01:49:06,522
- I don't wanna drive with him.
- Get her back in the car!

818
01:49:44,329 --> 01:49:46,763
You need to get him to slow down.

819
01:49:46,969 --> 01:49:48,641
Slow down.

820
01:49:48,809 --> 01:49:51,198
Jackson, please.

821
01:49:55,289 --> 01:49:58,440
Tell him he has got
to slow down this car!

822
01:49:58,609 --> 01:50:01,203
Jackson, slow down.

823
01:50:01,369 --> 01:50:04,645
- Let me out of your car!
- Edith, shut up!

824
01:50:04,809 --> 01:50:07,721
- Let me out!
- Shut up! Jackson!

825
01:50:07,929 --> 01:50:09,328
No!

826
01:50:09,889 --> 01:50:12,528
- Jackson!
- Let me out of this car!

827
01:50:12,689 --> 01:50:17,399
Get back in the car! Jackson,
you stop this car right now, Jackson!

828
01:50:17,609 --> 01:50:20,521
- Stop, Jackson.
- Stop this car!

